@@ -0,0 +1,18 @@
+# Codex Writer Findings — Unknown
+Chain: pssk-cv-b2-b-260420-v1r-260420-225855-537a
+
+## Findings
+1. [P1] Fix 6 still missing cancelled-order filtering in table totals — `CartView.jsx:514-522` sums every other guest order into `tableOrdersTotal`, and the per-guest `guestTotal` in the table section at `CartView.jsx:865` also reduces over all guest orders with no cancel guard. The file does not define `isCancelledOrder` anywhere, so cancelled orders still inflate both table and guest totals. FIX: add an `isCancelledOrder` helper or equivalent cancel predicate, skip cancelled orders in both totals, and include the helper in the `tableOrdersTotal` dependency array.
+2. [P1] Fix 2 pending/unconfirmed status handling is absent — `statusBuckets` at `CartView.jsx:456-466` still builds only `{ served, in_progress }`, there are no `isPending` or `isOrderPending` branches anywhere in the file, and `bucketOrder` at `CartView.jsx:1005` still renders only `['served', 'in_progress']`. As a result, B44 orders with status `'new'` never get the required amber pending bucket, and the required “pending last” ordering cannot happen. FIX: add `pending_unconfirmed` grouping, switch pending checks to `'new'` instead of `'submitted'`, and render buckets in `['served', 'in_progress', 'pending_unconfirmed']` order.
+3. [P1] Fix 3 terminal-screen persistence is not implemented — the V8 “Ничего не ждёте” branch at `CartView.jsx:928-998` is driven only by in-memory bucket/cart state. `terminalStateShownForVersion`, `terminalVersion`, and any localStorage read/write for this state are missing from the file, so the terminal screen resets after reload instead of staying durable for the shown version. FIX: add versioned terminal-state memo/state plus localStorage persistence without changing the locked UI content.
+4. [P2] Fix 4 flat guest cards is still on the old grouped layout — `CartView.jsx:833-889` still renders a single expandable “Заказы стола” wrapper with `otherGuestsExpanded`, a shared table total, and nested guest blocks inside it. The required flat structure `otherGuestIdsFromOrders.map((gid) => <Card key={gid}>...)` is not present, so the table tab still violates the locked per-guest-card layout. FIX: remove the wrapper card/button and render one standalone card per guest while preserving the existing guest order rows inside each card.
+5. [P2] Fix 5 footer CTA is still the old filled button and has no helper row — the empty-cart/table footer at `CartView.jsx:1216-1222` still renders a solid button with `text-white` and `style={{backgroundColor: primaryColor}}`, and there is no `cart.cta.need_help_or_bill` helper text under it. The locked outline CTA plus inline bell helper is therefore missing. FIX: switch this branch to `variant="outline"`, remove the filled-button styling, and add the helper paragraph with inline `<Bell className="inline w-4 h-4 align-middle" />`.
+
+## Summary
+Total: 5 findings (0 P0, 3 P1, 2 P2, 0 P3)
+
+## Prompt Clarity (MANDATORY — do NOT skip this section)
+- Overall clarity: 3
+- Ambiguous Fix descriptions (list Fix # and what was unclear): None. The individual Fix 2-6 descriptions were specific.
+- Missing context (what info would have helped): The prompt assumes the working file matches the 1316-line `260419-00 CartView RELEASE.jsx`, but the actual `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx` in this workspace is a different 1115-line variant. It also requires Read/Write/Bash tools and absolute pipeline writes that are not available in this sandbox.
+- Scope questions (anything you weren't sure if it's in scope): The prompt mixes review-only instructions with implementation steps (`cp`, `wc -l`, fix-application order, mandatory `git reset --hard`). The main scope question was whether to review the current `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx` or a copied `260419-00` RELEASE snapshot. I reviewed the current target file in place because the prompt explicitly says to read the target file yourself and not apply fixes.
